<Link id="l01660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1660"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Build the location list for all DBG&#95;VALUEs in the function that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1661"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// describe the same variable. The resulting DebugLocEntries will have</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1662"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// strict monotonically increasing begin addresses and will never</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1663"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// overlap. If the resulting list has only one entry that is valid</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1664"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// throughout variable&#39;s scope return true.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1665"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01666" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1666"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// See the definition of DbgValueHistoryMap::Entry for an explanation of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01667" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1667"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// different kinds of history map entries. One thing to be aware of is that if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1668"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a debug value is ended by another entry (rather than being valid until the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1669"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// end of the function), that entry&#39;s instruction may or may not be included in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01670" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1670"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the range, depending on if the entry is a clobbering entry (it has an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01671" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1671"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction that clobbers one or more preceding locations), or if it is an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1672"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (overlapping) debug value entry. This distinction can be seen in the example</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1673"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// below. The first debug value is ended by the clobbering entry 2, and the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01674" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1674"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// second and third debug values are ended by the overlapping debug value entry</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1675"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 4</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1676"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1677"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Input:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1678"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1679"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   History map entries &#91;type, end index, mi&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1680"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2187"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2188"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Examine all the instructions at the start of the function. This doesn&#39;t</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2336"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2337"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For this function, we try to find MBBs where the last source line in every</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2338"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// block predecessor matches the first line seen in the block itself; for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2339"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// every such MBB, we set is&#95;stmt=false on the first line in the block, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2340"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for every other block we set is&#95;stmt=true on the first line.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2341"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For example, if we have the block %bb.3, which has 2 predecesors %bb.1 and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2342"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// %bb.2:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2343"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   bb.1:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2344"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     $r3 = MOV64ri 12, debug-location !DILocation(line: 4)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2345"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     JMP %bb.3, debug-location !DILocation(line: 5)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2346"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   bb.2:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2347"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     $r3 = MOV64ri 24, debug-location !DILocation(line: 5)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2348"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     JMP %bb.3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2349"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   bb.3:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2350"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     $r2 = MOV64ri 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2351"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     $r1 = ADD $r2, $r3, debug-location !DILocation(line: 5)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2352"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When we examine %bb.3, we first check to see if it contains any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2353"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions with debug locations, and select the first such instruction;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2354"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in this case, the ADD, with line=5. We then examine both of its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2355"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// predecessors to see what the last debug-location in them is. For each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2356"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// predecessor, if they do not contain any debug-locations, or if the last</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2357"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// debug-location before jumping to %bb.3 does not have line=5, then the ADD</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2358"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in %bb.3 must use IsStmt. In this case, all predecessors have a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2359"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// debug-location with line=5 as the last debug-location before jumping to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2360"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// %bb.3, so we do not set is&#95;stmt for the ADD instruction - we know that</span></CodeLine>
